# TypeScript Standards

- Keep TypeScript strict-friendly: avoid `any` unless unavoidable.
- Prefer explicit return types for exported functions.
- Use `@/*` imports for project-root aliases where configured.
- Keep React Server Components server-side by default; add `"use client"` only for interactivity.
- Handle errors explicitly and return meaningful messages from route handlers.
